    "recap_headline": "The University of Texas at Austin Athletics",
    "recap_text": "AUSTIN, Texas \u2014\nIn his first career Southeastern Conference start,\nDylan Volantis\nrecorded a career-best 11 strikeouts to propel No. 2 Texas to an 8-2 win over Ole Miss at UFCU Disch-Falk Field on Sunday afternoon.\nVolantis (3-0) pitched six innings of one-run baseball, as the Longhorns (18-1, 2-1 SEC) secured their SEC-opening series over the Rebels (16-5, 1-2 SEC).\nThe 6-foot-6, 220-pound southpaw struck out multiple batters in four of the first five frames, punching out the side in the fifth.\nVolantis held Ole Miss to five hits and one walk over his career-high 102 pitches.\nRight-hander\nSam Cozart\n(1) tossed the final three innings to lock down his first career save. Cozart yielded one unearned run, punching out five of the last eight Rebels.\nIn the victory,\nCarson Tinney\nand\nCasey Borba\nboth smacked two-run homers.\nTinney finished 3-for-4 with three RBI, highlighted by his 465-foot shot that cleared the 32-foot \"monster\" in center. The catcher's first-inning blast pushed Texas in front, 2-0.\nMeanwhile, Borba notched his fourth multi-hit effort in his last five games, highlighted by his fourth home run of the week. The junior jacked a 419-foot rocket over the YETI Yard in left, ballooning the advantage to 5-0 in the fourth.\nSparked by the power display, the Longhorns raced out to a six-run advantage before the fifth inning.\nJudd Utermark registered a run-scoring single to put Ole Miss on the board, but Volantis limited the damage to one.\nTexas tacked on two insurance tallies in the sixth, capped off by Tinney's RBI base hit.\nThe Rebels plated an unearned run in the seventh, capitalizing on a defensive miscue.\nThe Longhorns close out their four-game home swing against Tarleton State on Tuesday. First pitch is set for 6:30 p.m."
  },
